results.label: 7 Up
results.description: 7 Up is a brand of a lemon-lime flavored non-caffeinated soft drink. The rights to the brand are held by Dr Pepper Snapple Group in the United States, and PepsiCo (or its licensees) in the rest of the world, including Puerto Rico, where the concentrate is manufactured at the Pepsi facility in Cidra. The 7 Up logo includes a red spot between the '7' and 'Up'; this red spot has been animated and used as a mascot for the brand as Cool Spot.

results.label: "Looked Up" Plus Four
results.description: "Looked Up" Plus Four is an EP by indie rock band The Like Young. It was released in 2002 by Kittridge Records.
